<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - REASSEMBLY - MAIN CASE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="10">
        <title>MAIN CASE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the drive gear bearing on drive gear and in stall bearing snap ring. Position thrust
                ring (with numbers up) on the drive gear,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300672">Figure 72</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300672" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300672" filename="../figg13/G1300672.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 72. Drive Gear Bearing on Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new oil seal in drive gear bearing retainer. Install the drive gear into the clutch
                housing. Position an installation sleeve (arrow) on the drive gear before installing the bearing
                retainer,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300673">Figure 73</hotlnk>. (Refer to General Disassembly instructions)
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300673" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300673" filename="../figg13/G1300673.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Drive Gear Bearing Retainer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil baffle,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300674">Figure 74</hotlnk>. Coat drive gear bearing retainer mounting surface with
                Loctite Gasket Eliminator (purple). Install oil baffle and bearing retainer, aligning the lubrication
                holes (arrow). Be sure to install the clutch return spring bracket (not illustrated). Refer to Torque
                Chartfor bolt torque values.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300674" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300674" filename="../figg13/G1300674.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Install Oil Baffle</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the clutch housing, drive gear face down, on the workbench,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300675">Figure 75</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300675" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300675" filename="../figg13/G1300675.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 75. Drive Gear Face Down</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install overdrive fork for 13MAH transmission or 5th/6th speed shift fork for 13MAG
                transmission if it was removed. Secure it with bolts,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300676">Figure 76</hotlnk>. Refer to Torque Chartfor proper torque values.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300676" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300676" filename="../figg13/G1300676.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Overdrive Fork</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next install the 5th/6th speed synchronizer. Shift it down toward the drive gear. This will
                aid align ment,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300677">Figure 77</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300677" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300677" filename="../figg13/G1300677.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. 5th/6th Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The countershaft is installed next. Tilting the countershaft toward the mainshaft is the
                easiest way to do this,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300678">Figure 78</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300678" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300678" filename="../figg13/G1300678.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Install Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the mainshaft with a hoist. While it is in the air, install 1st/2nd and 3rd/4th speed
                forks into place,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300679">Figure 79</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300679" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300679" filename="../figg13/G1300679.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. 1st/2nd and 3rd/4th Speed Forks</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Oil the pocket bearing, then slide the mainshaft assembly into place. It may be necessary to
                tip the countershaft away from the mainshaft to do this. Make sure the shift bars line up with the shift
                bar support in the case,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300680">Figure 80</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300680" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300680" filename="../figg13/G1300680.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Slide Mainshaft Assembly In Place</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the housing sealing surface with Loctite Gasket Eliminator (purple). Lower the case
                into place with the help of a chain hoist. Install bolts and torque to values listed in Torque Chart.
                Re-install oil trough if it was removed,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300681">Figure 81</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300681" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300681" filename="../figg13/G1300681.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Lower Case Into Place</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
